  "Prerequisites": "Learners should have a basic familiarity with everyday workplace communication tools (such as email, messaging platforms, or video conferencing software) and a general awareness that AI-powered features are increasingly built into these tools.",
  "Learning objectives": "By the end of this course, you will be able to identify the key risks associated with using AI tools in meetings, chats, and internal communications, and explain how sensitive or confidential information can be unintentionally exposed. You will also be able to apply practical strategies to protect organisational data and make informed decisions about when and how to use AI tools responsibly in the workplace.",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "lesson title": "AI and Confidential Conversations",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores the risks that arise when AI tools are used during meetings, chat conversations, and internal communications. Many people are unaware that AI-powered features built into everyday workplace tools may be recording, analysing, or storing sensitive information without explicit consent. You will learn how to identify situations where confidential data could be exposed, and what steps you can take to protect yourself and your organisation. The lesson offers practical guidance to help you make informed decisions about when and how to use AI tools responsibly in professional settings. No prior technical knowledge is required, making this an accessible starting point for anyone who wants to use AI more safely at work.",
      "status": "draft",
      "content": "Risks of using AI tools in meetings, chats, and internal communications.",
